# ADR: Merchant Post-Purchase Webhook System

## Status

**Draft** - Pending Review

## Context

The commerce platform currently operates via synchronous request-response patterns where merchants receive order data only at checkout completion. There is no mechanism for merchants to notify the platform about post-purchase order changes (shipments, cancellations, refunds, etc.).

For agentic commerce scenarios, LLM partners need visibility into order lifecycle events so AI agents can proactively inform customers about their orders without requiring the customer to ask.

**Architecture Principle**: These webhooks are lightweight proxies. Merchants send order updates → Lambda validates and transforms → forwards to LLM partner. Minimal business logic.

## Decision

Implement a webhook ingestion system using AWS Lambda functions following the established handler patterns in `commerce-orchestrator/lambda/`.

### Webhook Event Types

| Event Type            | Description                        | Trigger Scenario                  |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| `ORDER_RECEIVED`      | Order received and being processed | Merchant confirms order receipt   |
| `ORDER_SHIPPED`       | Order has shipped with tracking    | Carrier pickup or first scan      |
| `ORDER_DELIVERED`     | Order delivered to customer        | Carrier delivery confirmation     |
| `ORDER_CANCELLED`     | Order cancelled before shipment    | Merchant or customer cancellation |
| `ORDER_REFUNDED`      | Full or partial refund issued      | Refund processed                  |
| `ITEM_RETURNED`       | Item(s) returned to merchant       | Return received/processed         |
| `FULFILLMENT_DELAYED` | Shipping delay notification        | Expected delivery changed         |

### System Architecture

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Merchant as Merchant System
    participant ALB as Public ALB
    participant Lambda as Webhook Lambda
    participant LLM as LLM Partner

    Merchant->>ALB: POST /v1/webhooks/post-purchase
    Note right of Merchant: { id, type, timestamp,<br/>merchant_order_number, payload }

    ALB->>Lambda: Forward request

    Lambda->>Lambda: Authenticate merchant
    Lambda->>Lambda: Validate payload (Zod)
    Lambda->>Lambda: Track metrics (CloudWatch)
    Lambda->>Lambda: Transform to partner schema

    Lambda->>LLM: POST notification
    Note right of Lambda: { id, type, timestamp,<br/>order_context, update_summary,<br/>structured_data }

    LLM-->>Lambda: 200 OK
    Lambda-->>ALB: 202 Accepted
    ALB-->>Merchant: 202 Accepted
    Note left of Merchant: { received: true, id }
```

## Data Schema Design

### Layer 1: Merchant Request Schema (Inbound)

What merchants send to us.

#### Base Event Fields

| Field                   | Type                 | Required | Description                                                                                            |
| ----------------------- | -------------------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `id`                    | string (UUID)        | Yes      | Unique identifier for this event (used for idempotency)                                                |
| `type`                  | enum                 | Yes      | One of: `ORDER_RECEIVED`, `ORDER_SHIPPED`, `ORDER_DELIVERED`, `ORDER_CANCELLED`, `FULFILLMENT_DELAYED` |
| `timestamp`             | string (ISO 8601)    | Yes      | When the event occurred                                                                                |
| `merchant_order_number` | string (1-256 chars) | Yes      | Merchant's order identifier (links to original checkout)                                               |
| `payload`               | object               | Yes      | Event-specific data (see below)                                                                        |

#### Event Payloads

**ORDER_RECEIVED**

| Field                     | Type              | Required | Description                   |
| ------------------------- | ----------------- | -------- | ----------------------------- |
| `estimated_ship_date`     | string (ISO 8601) | No       | When merchant expects to ship |
| `estimated_delivery_date` | string (ISO 8601) | No       | Projected delivery date       |

**ORDER_SHIPPED**

| Field                     | Type              | Required | Description                  |
| ------------------------- | ----------------- | -------- | ---------------------------- |
| `carrier`                 | string            | Yes      | Shipping carrier name        |
| `tracking_number`         | string            | Yes      | Carrier tracking number      |
| `tracking_url`            | string (URL)      | Yes      | Direct link to tracking page |
| `estimated_delivery_date` | string (ISO 8601) | No       | Expected delivery date       |

**ORDER_DELIVERED**

| Field            | Type              | Required | Description        |
| ---------------- | ----------------- | -------- | ------------------ |
| `delivered_date` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes      | Delivery timestamp |

**ORDER_CANCELLED**

| Field          | Type   | Required | Description              |
| -------------- | ------ | -------- | ------------------------ |
| `cancelled_by` | enum   | Yes      | `MERCHANT` or `CUSTOMER` |
| `reason`       | string | No       | Cancellation reason      |

**FULFILLMENT_DELAYED**

| Field                              | Type              | Required | Description                |
| ---------------------------------- | ----------------- | -------- | -------------------------- |
| `original_estimated_delivery_date` | string (ISO 8601) | Yes      | Previous delivery estimate |
| `new_estimated_delivery_date`      | string (ISO 8601) | Yes      | Updated delivery estimate  |
| `reason`                           | string            | No       | Reason for delay           |

